{"author":{"id":"b78c39e7b13f90a5827abfba043255fe7a4ede1499df23f110fffe5abfa44adc"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1770137866,"nonce":"6die1EgaIcB7CpeIe4R2Unx9J18=","metadata":{"github-id":"I_kwDOQ241x87n_r-6","github-url":"https://github.com/rolker/ros2_agent_workspace/issues/150","origin":"github"},"title":"Implement track lifecycle management (archive/restore)","message":"## Summary\n\nImplement track lifecycle management capabilities inspired by Conductor's `/conductor:manage` command, allowing completed features to be archived with lessons learned and restored if needed.\n\n## Parent Issue\n\nSub-issue of #139\n\n## Motivation\n\nCurrently, completed issues just close on GitHub with no structured way to:\n- Capture lessons learned from the implementation\n- Archive completed work with searchable metadata\n- Restore archived features if they need to be revisited\n- List what features are active vs archived\n\nConductor provides track management (archive, restore, delete, rename) that helps maintain a clean project state while preserving history.\n\n## Proposed Solution\n\n### Archive Script\n\n**File**: `.agent/scripts/archive_feature.sh`\n\n```bash\n# Archive a completed feature with lessons learned\n#\n# Usage: archive_feature.sh --issue \u003cnumber\u003e --reason \"completed successfully\"\n#\n# Creates: .agent/archive/ISSUE-\u003cnumber\u003e/\n#   - summary.md (auto-generated from PR/commits)\n#   - lessons_learned.md (user input or auto-generated)\n#   - metadata.json (timestamps, agent, outcome)\n```\n\n### List Script\n\n**File**: `.agent/scripts/list_features.sh`\n\n```bash\n# List active and archived features\n#\n# Usage: \n#   list_features.sh              # Active features\n#   list_features.sh --archived   # Archived features\n#   list_features.sh --all        # Both\n```\n\n### Restore Script\n\n**File**: `.agent/scripts/restore_feature.sh`\n\n```bash\n# Restore an archived feature for further work\n#\n# Usage: restore_feature.sh --issue \u003cnumber\u003e\n```\n\n### Archive Structure\n\n```\n.agent/archive/\n├── README.md\n└── ISSUE-139/\n    ├── summary.md        # What was built, key changes\n    ├── lessons_learned.md # What worked, what didn't, future suggestions\n    └── metadata.json     # {archived_at, archived_by, reason, pr_number, commits}\n```\n\n## Tasks\n\n### Phase 1: Archive Capability\n- [ ] Create `.agent/archive/` directory with README\n- [ ] Implement `archive_feature.sh`\n- [ ] Auto-generate summary from PR description and commits\n- [ ] Prompt for or auto-generate lessons learned\n\n### Phase 2: List and Restore\n- [ ] Implement `list_features.sh`\n- [ ] Implement `restore_feature.sh`\n- [ ] Add to CLI_COMMANDS.md\n\n### Phase 3: Integration\n- [ ] Add Makefile targets\n- [ ] Add to post-merge workflow suggestion\n- [ ] Document in CONTRIBUTING.md\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] Can archive a completed feature with metadata\n- [ ] Can list active and archived features\n- [ ] Can restore archived features\n- [ ] Archive preserves useful context for future reference\n- [ ] Works with all agent frameworks\n\n## Effort Estimate\n\n**Medium** (4-5 hours)\n\n## Priority\n\n**Low** - Nice to have, not blocking current workflows\n\n---\n**🤖 Authored-By**: `Copilot CLI Agent`\n**🧠 Model**: `Claude Opus 4.5`","files":null}]}